The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on temporal difference methods, which are commonly used in the field of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the estimation of functions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of moments to estimate functions is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of Taylor expansion, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a modified TD algorithm, which falls under the category of optimization and control (cs.LO).
